Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Trim the @green beans{80%g}. Cut into thirds.

Pour the boiling water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @basmati rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} and green beans, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

Next, add the @peri peri seasoning{1%sachet} and @tomato puree{30%g} to the chicken. Stir-fry, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @smoky base paste{1%sachet}, @butter{20%g}, @honey{1%tbsp} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce.

> See pantry for all three sauce ingredients.

Bring to a boil. Simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle of the chicken.

Add the rice to the chicken. Stir well to coat. Taste and season with salt and @?ground black pepper{} if needed.

Share between your #bowls{}. Top with the @soured cream{75%g}.

Enjoy!